  Both rejected in favor of the free-helper closure.

## Hints for Future Agents
- CRITICAL INVARIANT (documented in _make_page_fetcher docstring): the cache
  closure must NOT capture the PaginatedIterator. It closes over fetch_func +
  page_size only. If a future change makes fetch_func a bound method of the
  iterator, or otherwise captures self, the leak/cycle returns AND ruff B019
  will not flag it (the decorator is on a nested function, not a method).
- The weakref release test is the guardrail; keep it.

## Codebase Discoveries
- fetch_func built by make_calls_iterator (call.py) closes over server/
  project_id/filter -- never the iterator -- which is why the helper approach
  is leak-free here.

